The Old Boys Association of Kings College, Lagos, has outlined plans to mark the school’s 2018 Founder’s Day celebration. According to the chairman of the planning committee, Mr Mustapha Chike Obi, the celebration will be very memorable for members and guests. “The school will kick off the celebrations with activities from 18thSeptember and end on 20th September. The Old Boys’ activities, however, start on the 20th and end on the 23rd. It is called Kings Week. It is what the old boys association sponsors and directs. We have a lecture on the 20th. We have Jummat and Church service on Friday, and this will be followed by a dinner on the 22nd. We will be concluding with the AGM on the 23rd,” declared Obi.